'A lot of these provisions and penalties discriminate against women. Stoning to death normally has ahuge impact on women because more often than not they are found guilty of these crimes.'

This week celebrities, including U.S. television personality Ellen DeGeneres and British actor Stephen Fry, announced will be boycotting the hotel chain owned by the sultan on grounds thatthe new laws criminalised homosexuality.

