Gay rights organisations in the Asia Pacific have condemned the move to Sharia law.

'It may open the floodgates for further human rights violations against women, children, and other people on the basis of sexual orientation and gender identity,' two such groups wrote in the Malaysian Insider.

'Penalty by death sentence contravenes several international human rights laws.

